<h1>Getting started</h1>

<p>Nxt isn't on NuGet.org yet — install via the bootstrap script for your platform.</p>

<h2>1. Clone &amp; install</h2>
<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/Tyler-Harker/Nxt.git
cd Nxt

# Linux:
./install-linux

# macOS:
./install-macos

# Windows (PowerShell):
.\install-windows.ps1</code></pre>

<p>
    The script packs <code>Nxt.Runtime</code>, <code>Nxt.Cli</code>, and
    <code>Nxt.Templates</code>, registers <code>./nupkg</code> as a NuGet source, installs
    the CLI globally, and adds <code>~/.dotnet/tools</code> to PATH if missing.
</p>

<h2>2. Scaffold an app</h2>
<pre><code>nxt new my-app
cd my-app
nxt dev          # http://localhost:5000</code></pre>

<h2>3. The generated layout</h2>
<pre><code>my-app/
├── Program.cs               # one line: await NxtHost.RunAsync(args);
├── Pages/
│   ├── Index.razor          → /
│   └── About.cshtml         → /about
├── Api/
│   └── HelloEndpoint.cs     → /api/hello
└── Middleware/
    └── (auto-registered classes with [Middleware])</code></pre>

<h2>4. Updating</h2>
<p>To pull the latest source and reinstall everything in one shot:</p>
<pre><code>nxt update</code></pre>
<p>
    Options: <code>--repo &lt;url&gt;</code> for a fork, <code>--branch &lt;name&gt;</code>
    for a specific branch.
</p>
